<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19474] Wrong placement of WARN log for truncation below HWM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19474</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ReplicaFetcherThread#truncate&lt;/tt&gt; has a useful &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/da4fbba2793528e283458e080a690ad141857b0b/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaFetcherThread.scala#L171&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;WARN log&lt;/a&gt; when a follower is truncating its log segment below its HWM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is of particular help when debugging data loss scenarios like those described in the motivation for &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-966%3A+Eligible+Leader+Replicas&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;KIP-966&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, a refactoring in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/5608/files#diff-693a5eaaaa4fe61a18af23d5b06ccc024261dda01558cbaacb7020e1911c6d55R264&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PR 5608&lt;/a&gt; moved the check to &lt;em&gt;after&lt;/em&gt; the truncation, which may modify the HWM. As a result, the log may not be emitted even though the log is truncated below the HWM&lt;/p&gt;</description>
